  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Immediate Lifesaving Emergency Shelter and Non-food Item (NFI) Assistance for Cyclone Affected Populations in Nampula and Zambezia Provinces, Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 11 March 2022, Tropical Cyclone Gombe made landfall in Mozambique with gusts of winds between 165 and 230 km/h. The storm brought heavy rainfall and intense winds mainly affecting the provinces of Nampula and Zambezia, but also the provinces of Niassa, Tete and Sofala. The storm caused flash floods, landslides, and flooding as it moved further inland. According to the National Institute for Disaster Management and Risk Reduction (INGD) more than 736,015 people in Mozambique have been affected by the storm. Under this project, IOM is increasing the capacity of Shelter Cluster partners to respond and address the immediate shelter and non-food item needs of internally displaced persons (IDPs) and other affected communities in the provinces of Nampula and Zambezia, affected by Tropical Cyclone Gombe.</narrative>
  </description>
